forts to build a new, global, and economically dominant India. The ways they accept and resist the premises and conditions of their work offer new potentials for alternative visions of living and working in neoliberal economies. Demonstrating how these coders' cognitive labor realigns and reimagines race and class, Amrute conceptualizes personhood and migration within global capitalism in new ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aComputer programmerszGermanyzBerlin. 0aComputer programmerszIndia. 0aEast IndianszGermanyzBerlin. 0aForeign workers, East IndianzGermanyzBerlin. 0aInformation technologyzGermanyzBerlinxEmployees. 4aAAA Book Award winners. 4aAAA General Anthropology section. 4aDiana Forsythe award winner. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374275zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374275.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles